Title: Avatar: The Way of Water
Plot Summary: Jake Sully lives with his newfound family formed on the extrasolar moon Pandora. Once a familiar threat returns to finish what was previously started, Jake must work with Neytiri and the army of the Na'vi race to protect their home.

Title: The Menu
Plot Summary: A young couple travels to a remote island to eat at an exclusive restaurant where the chef has prepared a lavish menu, with some shocking surprises.

Title: Babylon
Plot Summary: A tale of outsized ambition and outrageous excess, it traces the rise and fall of multiple characters during an era of unbridled decadence and depravity in early Hollywood.

Title: Everything Everywhere All at Once
Plot Summary: A middle-aged Chinese immigrant is swept up into an insane adventure in which she alone can save existence by exploring other universes and connecting with the lives she could have led.

Title: M3GAN
Plot Summary: A robotics engineer at a toy company builds a life-like doll that begins to take on a life of its own.

Title: The Banshees of Inisherin
Plot Summary: Two lifelong friends find themselves at an impasse when one abruptly ends their relationship, with alarming consequences for both of them.

Title: Puss in Boots: The Last Wish

Title: Triangle of Sadness
Plot Summary: A fashion model celebrity couple join an eventful cruise for the super-rich.

Title: Glass Onion
Plot Summary: Famed Southern detective Benoit Blanc travels to Greece for his latest case.

Title: The Whale
Plot Summary: A reclusive, morbidly obese English teacher attempts to reconnect with his estranged teenage daughter.

Title: Tár

Title: Shotgun Wedding
Plot Summary: Darcy and Tom gather their families for the ultimate destination wedding but when the entire wedding party is taken hostage the bride and groom must save their loved ones--if they don't kill each other first.

Title: All Quiet on the Western Front

Title: A Man Called Otto

Title: Aftersun

Title: Women Talking

Title: X

Title: Bullet Train

Title: Elvis

Title: Devotion
Plot Summary: A pair of U.S. Navy fighter pilots risk their lives during the Korean War and become some of the Navy's most celebrated wingmen.

Title: To Leslie

Title: Vengeance
Plot Summary: A writer from New York City attempts to solve the murder of a girl he hooked up with and travels down south to investigate the circumstances of her death and discover what happened to her.

Title: Amsterdam
Plot Summary: In the 1930s, three friends witness a murder, are framed for it, and uncover one of the most outrageous plots in American history.

Title: RRR
Plot Summary: A fictitious story about two legendary revolutionaries and their journey away from home before they started fighting for their country in the 1920s.

Title: Black Panther: Wakanda Forever

Title: Violent Night
Plot Summary: When a group of mercenaries attack the estate of a wealthy family, Santa Claus must step in to save the day (and Christmas).

Title: The Batman
Plot Summary: When a sadistic serial killer begins murdering key political figures in Gotham, Batman is forced to investigate the city's hidden corruption and question his family's involvement.

Title: Vesper

Title: Blonde

Title: Guillermo del Toro's Pinocchio
Plot Summary: A father's wish magically brings a wooden boy to life in Italy, giving him a chance to care for the child.

Title: Barbarian

Title: Black Adam

Title: Skinamarink

Title: Living

Title: Don't Worry Darling

Title: Pearl

Title: Where the Crawdads Sing

Title: The Northman

Title: Sick

Title: Nope

Title: White Noise

Title: Smile

Title: Causeway

Title: Fall

Title: Scream

Title: Decision to Leave

Title: Empire of Light

Title: Bones and All

Title: Thor: Love and Thunder

Title: The Wonder

Title: Strange World
Plot Summary: The legendary Clades are a family of explorers whose differences threaten to topple their latest and most crucial mission.

Title: Ticket to Paradise

Title: Candy Land

Title: Men

Title: Poker Face

Title: The Invitation
Plot Summary: A young woman is courted and swept off her feet, only to realize a gothic conspiracy is afoot.

Title: The Good Nurse
Plot Summary: An infamous caregiver is implicated in the deaths of hundreds of hospital patients.

Title: The Price We Pay
Plot Summary: After a pawn shop robbery goes askew, two criminals take refuge at a remote farmhouse to try to let the heat die down, but find something much more menacing.

Title: Death on the Nile
Plot Summary: While on vacation on the Nile, Hercule Poirot must investigate the murder of a young heiress.

Title: Pinocchio
Plot Summary: A puppet is brought to life by a fairy, who assigns him to lead a virtuous life in order to become a real boy.

Title: Alice, Darling
Plot Summary: A young woman trapped in an abusive relationship becomes the unwitting participant in an intervention staged by her two closest friends.

Title: Lady Chatterley's Lover
Plot Summary: An unhappily married aristocrat begins a torrid affair with the gamekeeper on her husband's country estate.

Title: The Son
Plot Summary: Peter has his busy life with new partner Beth and their baby thrown into disarray when his ex-wife Kate turns up with their teenage son, Nicholas.

Title: The Offering
Plot Summary: A family struggling with loss find themselves at the mercy of an ancient demon trying to destroy them from the inside.

Title: The Lost City
Plot Summary: A reclusive romance novelist on a book tour with her cover model gets swept up in a kidnapping attempt that lands them both in a cutthroat jungle adventure.

Title: EO

Title: Drishyam 2
Plot Summary: A gripping tale of an investigation and a family which is threatened by it. Will Vijay Salgaonkar be able to protect his family this time?

Title: Prey

Title: Ambulance
Plot Summary: Two robbers steal an ambulance after their heist goes awry.

Title: The School for Good and Evil

Title: Firestarter
Plot Summary: A young girl tries to understand how she mysteriously gained the power to set things on fire with her mind.

Title: Emancipation
Plot Summary: A runaway slave forges through the swamps of Louisiana on a tortuous journey to escape plantation owners that nearly killed him.

Title: Fantastic Beasts: The Secrets of Dumbledore
Plot Summary: Professor Albus Dumbledore must assist Newt Scamander and his partners as Grindelwald begins to lead an army to eliminate all Muggles.

Title: Speak No Evil

Title: Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness

They seek help from Wanda the Scarlet Witch, Wong and others.

Title: The Swimmers

Title: The Stranger

Title: The Sea Beast
Plot Summary: When a young girl stows away on the ship of a legendary sea monster hunter, they launch an epic journey into uncharted waters - and make history to boot.

Title: One Way
Plot Summary: Freddy, a petty criminal, is on the run with a bag full of cash and coke. He's way over his head and hurt bad. With a bullet in his guts he's running out of time.

Title: Mrs. Harris Goes to Paris

Title: Turning Red

Title: Luckiest Girl Alive
Plot Summary: A woman in New York, who seems to have things under control, is faced with a trauma that makes her life unravel.

Title: Good Mourning
Plot Summary: Follows London Clash, a movie star whose world is turned upside down when he must choose between pursuing his one true love and landing a life-changing, starring role in a major motion picture.

Title: The Outfit

Title: The Amazing Maurice

Title: The People We Hate at the Wedding
Plot Summary: Family tensions ramp up among siblings in the week leading up to their half-sister's wedding in the country.

Title: Fresh
Plot Summary: FRESH follows Noa (Daisy Edgar-Jones), who meets the alluring Steve (Sebastian Stan) at a grocery store and - given her frustration with dating apps - takes a chance and gives him her number.

Title: Moonfall
Plot Summary: A mysterious force knocks the moon from its orbit and sends it hurtling on a collision course toward earth.

Title: Hustle
Plot Summary: A basketball scout discovers a phenomenal street ball player while in Spain and sees the prospect as his opportunity to get back into the NBA.

Title: Do Revenge
Plot Summary: Drea and Eleanor agree to go after one another's bullies.

Title: Disenchanted
Plot Summary: Fifteen years after her happily ever after, Giselle questions her happiness, inadvertently turning the lives of those in the real world and Andalasia upside down in the process.

Title: Lyle, Lyle, Crocodile
Plot Summary: Feature film based on the children's book about a crocodile that lives in New York City.

Title: Broker
Plot Summary: Boxes are left out for people to anonymously drop off their unwanted babies.

Title: The Bubble
Plot Summary: A group of actors and actresses stuck inside a pandemic bubble at a hotel attempt to complete a film.

Title: Thirteen Lives
Plot Summary: A rescue mission is assembled in Thailand where a group of young boys and their soccer coach are trapped in a system of underground caves that are flooding.

Title: What's Love Got to Do with It?
Plot Summary: A cross-cultural romantic comedy.

Title: God's Crooked Lines
Plot Summary: Follows a woman checking into a psychiatric ward to investigate a homicide.

Title: Corsage

Title: Troll
Plot Summary: Deep in the Dovre mountain, something gigantic wakes up after a thousand years in captivity. The creature destroys everything in its path and quickly approaches Oslo.

Title: Lou
Plot Summary: A storm rages. A young girl is kidnapped. Her mother teams up with the mysterious woman next door to pursue the kidnapper, a journey that tests their limits and exposes shocking secrets from their pasts.

Title: Prey for the Devil
Plot Summary: A nun prepares to perform an exorcism and comes face to face with a demonic force with mysterious ties to her past.

Title: The Hanging Sun
Plot Summary: On the run from his former employer, a reluctant hitman seeks refuge in an isolated village where he is faced with events that test the true nature of his conscience.

Title: Unwelcome

Title: Deep Water
Plot Summary: A well-to-do husband who allows his wife to have affairs in order to avoid a divorce becomes a prime suspect in the disappearance of her lovers.

Title: Kantara
Plot Summary: It involves culture of Kambala and Bhootha Kola. A human and nature conflict where Shiva is a rebel who defends his village and nature. A death leads to war between villagers and evil forces. Will he be able to regain peace in the village?

Title: Memory
Plot Summary: An assassin-for-hire finds that he's become a target after he refuses to complete a job for a dangerous criminal organization.

Title: The Adam Project
Plot Summary: After accidentally crash-landing in 2022, time-traveling fighter pilot Adam Reed teams up with his 12-year-old self for a mission to save the future.

Title: Project Wolf Hunting

Title: Last Seen Alive

Title: Three Thousand Years of Longing

Title: Bros
Plot Summary: Two men with commitment problems attempt a relationship.

Title: Alkhallat+
Plot Summary: He who has a trick in their bag, they shall use it. An anthology of social deception and trickery in four unlikely places.

Title: Dog

Title: Spiderhead

Title: Slumberland

Title: Halloween Ends

Title: Hellraiser

Title: Catherine Called Birdy
Plot Summary: A 14 year old girl in medieval England navigates through life and avoiding potential suitors her father has in mind.

Title: Armageddon Time
Plot Summary: A deeply personal coming-of-age story about the strength of family and the generational pursuit of the American Dream.

Title: Marlowe

Title: Samaritan

Title: The Devil Conspiracy
Plot Summary: A cult steals the Shroud of Turin for wicked purposes.

Title: Orphan: First Kill
Plot Summary: After orchestrating a brilliant escape from an Estonian psychiatric facility, Esther travels to America by impersonating the missing daughter of a wealthy family.

Title: Watcher

Title: Beast

Title: Spin Me Round

Title: My Policeman

Title: Minions: The Rise of Gru

Title: The Lair
